      "valid": false,
      "violation": "ADR-125 D3′ (I2)",
      "note": "The 67-char fe701<x> form that omits the 0x02 even-y parity byte — does NOT round-trip to the key. The secp256k1-pub codec is defined over the 33-byte compressed point (02 ‖ X); the parity byte is load-bearing, not a separator. Length 71 with the 02 prefix is invariant. MUST be rejected."
